name: How to Write a Successful Resume and Cover Letter!
summary:
Your resume/CV and cover letter create a first impression, so you want them to be noticed by employers. Is your application at the professional standard expected by recruiters for internships and grad programs?
Come along to this session and find out How to write a strong Resume and Cover Letter!
details:
Your resume is your most important marketing tool. Learn how to market yourself effectively and get ahead of the crowd!

This 2 hour workshop will help you to prepare a professional resume and tailor your cover letter to reflect your skills, knowledge, education and achievements relevant to the job you are applying for.

This workshop will cover information on:

  1. Analysing a job ad & understanding what an employer wants
  2. What to include and how to format your resume
  3. The importance of a Cover Letter
  4. Cover letter Format and Content

This workshop requires you to bring your current resume. It doesn't matter whether it is your high school resume or a more recent one for a casual job.

This workshop is accessible to all UQ Students and Alumni of up to 6 months. Bookings are not required but please make sure to arrive on time to secure your seat. If we have reached full capacity you will be directed to the next available workshop.

*During the first 8 weeks of Semester it is advised you arrive at least 15 prior to start time.
venue:
Student Services, level 2, Building 21C, Media Room 215
2 hours

name: Interview Excellence: The steps to interview success
summary: Want to improve you interview skills? The workshop provides valuable information to help you nail your next interview and gives solid guidance on how to best prepare. Gain an insight into employer expectations while developing confidence in your unique skills and achievements.
details:
You have landed an interview and now the only thing between you and the job is how you sell yourself on the day!

This workshop will teach you how to prepare and present yourself at interview and increase your chances of securing the job.

This workshop will cover information on:

  • Researching for the role and how to better prepare yourself
  • General and behavioural interview questions/responses
  • How to handle the curly questions
  • Selling your skills and attributes to leave a positive lasting impression
venue:
Media Room 215
Student Union Complex, Bld 21C (directly under the Pizza Cafe)

name: Networking: Connecting with people to uncover new opportunites
summary: Did you know that over 75% of roles are not advertised? Crack the hidden job market by learning how to network, both professionally and in informal situations.
details:
This session will assist attendees with the practical steps of how to interact with industry representatives plus much more:

Conversations with industry: introductions, questions and ending conversation Professional networking in person and online – i.e. LinkedIn Informal networking- in person and online How to create a strong first impression Strategic networking This session is beneficial for all year levels.
venue: Student Services, level 2, Building 21C, Media Room 215 2 hours

name: Stress Management
summary: Competing demands and modern living have produced a life style that is fast paced and stressful. Keep your head above water by developing a repertoire of skills to maintain your ability to cope with your daily challenges.
details: Competing demands and modern living have produced a life style that is fast paced and stressful. Keep your head above water by developing a repertoire of skills to maintain your ability to cope with your daily challenges.

name: Getting Started
summary: This session will help you make a smooth transition to campus life and includes essential information you need to get settled in and off to a good start.  Learn some fun facts about UQ, explore your campus, and find practical information about enrolling, getting ID cards, and getting connected to other UQ students.

name: Referencing Correctly and Avoiding Plagiarism
summary:

For further information, check the myAdvisor site for information on academic integrity.
